text:
Honestly I don’t get the hate in the other reviews, I find their food really amazing for its affordable price.

Their signature boat noodles cost about $8.90. The soup is rich and flavourful, although the garlic skins does get in the way of you enjoying the soup towards the end.

I ate here around 8pm on a Wednesday so there wasn’t much of a crowd and it was a pretty chill place to dine.

Have ordered from here quite frequently (usually laksa or the beef boat noodles) throughout the past few years. Their meat quality seems to have dropped. Found a piece of bone INSIDE the meatball (I bit into it). Definitely not ordering again.

That Aunty so rude. Scold my mum when she ask to change the egg cause of the egg white is not cook. Transparent. Although we ask me half boil egg. Half boil not = to no cook. transparent egg white is not cook at all not half cook.
